Qualifications:
1. Master’s degree (U.S. or foreign equivalent) in Accounting, Accountancy, Finance, or related field, such as Financial Engineering and one (1) year of experience in the job offered or in a related role OR Bachelor’s degree (U.S. or foreign equivalent) in Accounting, Accountancy, Finance, or related field, such as Financial Engineering and three (3) years of experience in the job offered or in a related role.
2. Must have one (1) year of experience (with Master’s degree) OR three (3) years of experience (with Bachelor’s degree) with: applying technical knowledge of accounting and financial reporting concepts that can be applied to working on various regulatory reports for numerous swap dealers, SEC & CFTC regulatory financial filings;
3. coordinating projects related to the enhancement of controls and/or automation and conveying detailed complex financial reporting topics to key stakeholders at all levels;
4. working on various types of financial products, particularly derivatives;
5. performing analytical and problem-solving tasks for financial reporting, including analyzing reporting balance fluctuations and solving reconciliation issues.

